<Link id="l01340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1340"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// With the exception of data-predicate transitions, no instructions are</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1344"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  2 Most unpacked integer types are not legal and thus integer extends</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1346"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// These can make &quot;bitcasting&quot; a multiphase process. REINTERPRET&#95;CAST is used</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1347"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to transition between unpacked and packed types of the same element type,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1348"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// with BITCAST used otherwise.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1349"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This function does not handle predicate bitcasts.</span></CodeLine>
